<@U026103R3> <@U026PLK4S> <@U026PHQ3J> question about text for things like settings: For the android app, many of the settings only capitalize the first word ("Sign out" "Privacy policy", etc). The comp for the iOS app has these terms capitalized on each word ("Sign Out" "Privacy Policy" etc). Life would be significantly easier for localization if we matched android's strings. Can you guys let me know what you think? Thanks.
